Any node in `Konva` can have only ONE parent.
You can&#39;t add a shape into different containers. If you do this:

```
layer1.add(rect);
layer2.add(rect);
```

Then the `rect` will be removed from `layer1` and added into `layer2`.

So you have to create a second rectangle. If you want to have the same properties, you can clone the node:

```
layer1.add(rect);

const rect2 = rect.clone();
layer2.add(rect2);
```

